metadata.description:

Controls:

objkt.name: Improvisation I #62

metadata.name: Improvisation I #62
metadata.description:
“Improvisation I“ was born after my experiments with Fractal Brownian Motion. 

During random tweaks of colours, parameters and sizes I got something that really clicked with me — a picture I wanted to get out of the code some time ago. 

Painterly looking curves and blots with subtle colours transitions create a calming picture, sometimes resembling outlines of a landscape.

——————

To change the size of an image, open it in live view and add ‘&size=[size (6800 max.)]’ to the end of the URL. 
Press [C] to load a clean version without grain.
Press [S] to save the image.

Created using p5.js and GLSL.
License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0.

——————

hrunz. — Oct. 2022.

issuer.name: Improvisation I

objkt.name: Collapse #164

metadata.name: Collapse #164
metadata.description:
The Impossibility of Representing Something Spherical Flat

A sphere collapses to a flat plane, revealing the transformations and stretching required for such an operation. How to represent something spherical flat? How to see what's not there, or how to see it differently? 

Released on the occasion of the Tribute to Herbert W. Franke.  
50% of the primary sales will be donated to the Foundation Herbert W. Franke.

each celebrity has been hand crafted for ideal cultural impact, with varying deformities, goiters and impacted hairs grown thoughtfully from the medical waste of other celebrities who are also desperate for another insufferable attention grab. they’ve sacrificed themselves for you. because you didn’t have what it took to build something. so do what you need to do. for them. by buying their deformed, barely sentient heads to worship at. it would really make them feel better. and there’s nothing worse than an upset genetically modified celebrity and brand collaboration corpse.

feed them. grow them. wonder if this means anything at all. drink from the never ending drain of reheated influencer bath water. die with the most likes.
